    "The authors report that the second stage involves model fine-tuning using reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF).",
    "However, further details on the training set are not described due to concerns surrounding safety implications and the \"competitive landscape.\"",
    "The training set's characteristics are widely acknowledged for contributing significantly to biases introduced during model development and may have significant implications for patient outcomes [11, 24].",
    "Further, using RLHF is a helpful tool to increase the appropriateness of responses by a model.",
    "However, depending on the demographics and agendas of labelers, specific responses will be favored over another."
